  1. Oxford 3000
  2. Oxford 14

Words 1301-1400

  1. I
    - I am happy to see you today.

  2. ice
    - The ice on the lake is very thick.

  3. idea
    - She has a great idea for the project.

  4. ideal
    - This house is an ideal place to live.

  5. identify
    - Can you identify the person in the photo?

  6. identity
    - He kept his identity a secret.

  7. if
    - If it rains, we will stay inside.

  8. ignore
    - Please do not ignore the warning signs.

  9. ill
    - She is feeling ill and needs to rest.

  10. illegal
    - It is illegal to park here without a permit.

  11. illness
    - His illness kept him in bed for a week.

  12. illustrate
    - The teacher used a diagram to illustrate the concept.

  13. illustration
    - The book has beautiful illustrations on every page.

  14. image
    - The image on the screen is very clear.

  15. imaginary
    - The story is about an imaginary world.

  16. imagination
    - Use your imagination to solve the problem.

  17. imagine
    - Can you imagine living on another planet?

  18. immediate
    - We need an immediate response to the situation.

  19. immediately
    - She left the room immediately after the meeting.

  20. immigrant
    - The immigrant worked hard to build a new life.

  21. impact
    - The new policy will have a big impact on the economy.

  22. impatient
    - He was impatient while waiting for the bus.

  23. imply
    - His words imply that he is not happy with the decision.

  24. import
    - The company plans to import goods from Europe.

  25. importance
    - She understands the importance of education.

  26. important
    - It is important to eat healthy food.

  27. impose
    - The government will impose new taxes next year.

  28. impossible
    - It is impossible to finish the work in one day.

  29. impress
    - He wants to impress his boss with his work.

  30. impressed
    - I was impressed by her performance.

  31. impression
    - His first impression of the city was positive.

  32. impressive
    - The view from the top of the mountain is impressive.

  33. improve
    - She wants to improve her English skills.

  34. improvement
    - There has been a big improvement in his grades.

  35. in
    - The keys are in the drawer.

  36. inch
    - The table is 36 inches wide.

  37. incident
    - The police are investigating the incident.

  38. include
    - The price includes breakfast and dinner.

  39. included
    - The package included a map and a guidebook.

  40. including
    - Everyone was there, including the new manager.

  41. income
    - His income is enough to support his family.

  42. increase
    - The company plans to increase its production next year.

  43. increasingly
    - People are becoming increasingly aware of climate change.

  44. incredible
    - The view from the top of the hill is incredible.

  45. incredibly
    - She is incredibly talented at painting.

  46. indeed
    - The meal was indeed delicious.

  47. independent
    - She is an independent woman who runs her own business.

  48. indicate
    - The sign indicates the direction to the nearest hospital.

  49. indirect
    - He made an indirect comment about the issue.

  50. individual
    - Each individual has the right to express their opinion.

  51. indoor
    - We decided to have an indoor picnic because of the rain.

  52. indoors
    - It is too cold outside, so we stayed indoors.

  53. industrial
    - The city is known for its industrial development.

  54. industry
    - The tourism industry is growing rapidly.

  55. infection
    - The doctor prescribed medicine to treat the infection.

  56. influence
    - Her parents had a strong influence on her career choice.

  57. inform
    - Please inform me if there are any changes to the schedule.

  58. informal
    - The meeting was informal and relaxed.

  59. information
    - The website provides useful information about the event.

  60. ingredient
    - Sugar is an important ingredient in this recipe.

  61. initial
    - Her initial reaction was one of surprise.

  62. initially
    - Initially, he was not interested in the project.

  63. initiative
    - She took the initiative to organize the event.

  64. injure
    - He did not want to injure himself while playing sports.

  65. injured
    - The injured player was taken to the hospital.

  66. injury
    - He is recovering from a serious injury.

  67. inner
    - She found peace in her inner thoughts.

  68. innocent
    - The court found him innocent of the charges.

  69. insect
    - There is an insect on the window.

  70. inside
    - The children are playing inside the house.

  71. insight
    - The book provides insight into the history of the region.

  72. insist
    - She insists on paying for the meal.

  73. inspire
    - His story will inspire others to follow their dreams.

  74. install
    - They will install a new air conditioner in the office.

  75. instance
    - For instance, you can use this tool to edit photos.

  76. instead
    - We decided to stay home instead of going out.

  77. institute
    - The institute offers courses in computer science.

  78. institution
    - The institution is known for its excellent research.

  79. instruction
    - Follow the instruction carefully to complete the task.

  80. instructor
    - The instructor explained the lesson clearly.

  81. instrument
    - He plays a musical instrument in the band.

  82. insurance
    - The company provides health insurance for its employees.

  83. intelligence
    - Her intelligence and hard work helped her succeed.

  84. intelligent
    - He is an intelligent student who learns quickly.

  85. intend
    - I intend to finish the project by next week.

  86. intended
    - The book is intended for young readers.

  87. intense
    - The competition was intense but exciting.

  88. intention
    - Her intention was to help, not to criticize.

  89. interest
    - He has a strong interest in learning new languages.

  90. interested
    - She is interested in joining the art club.

  91. interesting
    - The movie was interesting and kept us entertained.

  92. internal
    - The company is dealing with some internal issues.

  93. international
    - The conference attracted international participants.

  94. internet
    - The internet is a great source of information.

  95. interpret
    - Can you interpret the meaning of this poem?

  96. interrupt
    - Please do not interrupt while I am speaking.

  97. interview
    - She prepared well for the job interview.

  98. into
    - He walked into the room with a smile.

  99. introduce
    - Let me introduce you to my friend.

  100. introduction
    - The introduction of the book gives an overview of the topic.
